For the organization, extract from the document:
- governance_roles: roles involved in AI governance (e.g. "AI Ethics Board", "Chief AI Officer", "Data Protection Officer")
- management_system: any management system referenced (e.g. "ISO 42001", "AIMS")
- certifications: relevant certifications or standards compliance
- delegates: entities the organization delegates AI governance responsibility to

For each stakeholder, determine from context:
- involvement: "intended" if they are meant to interact with the AI system, "unintended" if not
- activity: "active" if they actively use or operate the system, "passive" if they receive its effects
- awareness: "informed" if they know AI is involved, "uninformed" if not
- output_control: "challenge" if they can dispute AI output, "correct" if they can modify it, "cannot_opt_out" if they are bound by it
- relationship: "internal" to the organization or "external"
- interests: specific interests, concerns, or stakes they hold

For each AI system, determine from context:
- modality: input/output modality (e.g. "text-to-text", "image-to-text", "multimodal")
- techniques: AI techniques used (e.g. "deep learning", "transformer", "RAG", "rule-based")
- automation_level: level of automation (e.g. "fully automated", "human-in-the-loop", "advisory")

For each regulation, determine from context:
- jurisdiction: geographic or legal jurisdiction (e.g. "EU", "United States", "United Kingdom")
- reference: specific section, article, or version reference

Leave fields as empty strings if the document provides no evidence.

